nship with one another. When these organizations are divided into groups, like regional versus universal organizations, many new, seemingly contradictory, interpretations of international organizations law emerge. Through elaborate network representations, radar charters, k-clusters analyses and scatter plots, this book offers an unprecedented insight into the principles and values of international organizations.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aInternational agenciesxLaw and legislation. 0aInternational law. 7aLAW / International.2bisacsh  aempirical legal studies.  afounding constitutions.  ainternational organizations law.  ainternational organizations' constitutions.  ajurisprudence.  aorganizational principles.  aorganizational values.  apatterns of authority.  apublic international law.1 aMichael, Bryane, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aPushkarna, Natasha, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut40uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152615242840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526152428423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526152428/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles